            slug: 'iban-validator-and-parser',
            icon: Landmark,
            title: 'IBAN validator and parser',
            long_description:
                '<h2>What is IBAN validator and parser?</h2>\n<p>The IBAN validator and parser is an online tool designed to help you verify and understand International Bank Account Numbers (IBANs). Its primary purpose is to check if an IBAN is valid according to international standards and to break down the IBAN into its core components.</p>\n<p>You might want to use this tool to ensure that an IBAN you are using for a payment is correct, to verify an IBAN provided to you, or simply to understand the structure and details embedded within a specific IBAN.</p>\n\n<h2>How to use IBAN validator and parser</h2>\n<p>Using the IBAN validator and parser is straightforward and quick. Just follow these simple steps:</p>\n<ul>\n    <li>Go to the tool\'s page in your web browser.</li>\n    <li>Locate the input field designated for the IBAN.</li>\n    <li>Enter or paste the IBAN you wish to validate and parse into this field.</li>\n    <li>Click the button, usually labeled something like "Validate IBAN" or "Check IBAN".</li>\n    <li>The tool will process the IBAN instantly and display the results below the input field.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>The results will typically tell you if the IBAN is valid or invalid. If valid, it will also show you parsed information such as the country code, the Basic Bank Account Number (BBAN), whether it\'s a QR-IBAN, and provide the IBAN in a more readable, friendly format.</p>\n\n<h2>Use cases and applications</h2>\n<p>The IBAN validator and parser is a valuable utility for anyone dealing with international bank transfers or needing to process banking information. Here are a few practical scenarios where you can leverage this tool:</p>\n\n<h3>Sending International Payments</h3>\n<p>Before initiating an international money transfer, it\'s crucial to have the correct recipient details. Use this tool to quickly validate the provided IBAN. An invalid IBAN can lead to failed transfers, delays, and potentially costly bank fees. Checking it beforehand saves you time and prevents frustration.</p>\n\n<h3>Receiving Payments from Abroad</h3>\n<p>If you are expecting a payment from someone in another country, they will likely ask for your IBAN. Similarly, if you are receiving payments from clients or customers, you can use this tool to verify the IBANs they provide are correctly formatted and valid. This helps ensure the payment reaches you without issues.</p>\n\n<h3>Business Data Entry and Verification</h3>\n<p>Businesses that handle large volumes of international transactions or manage customer/supplier databases with banking information can use this tool for data verification. It helps maintain data accuracy by quickly identifying incorrectly entered or invalid IBANs, improving the reliability of financial records.</p>\n\n<h3>Software Development and Testing</h3>\n<p>Developers building applications or systems that handle international payments or require IBAN input can use this tool during the development and testing phases. It provides a quick way to test their own validation logic against a reliable external source and understand how valid and invalid IBANs are structured and parsed.</p>\n\n<h2>Benefits and features</h2>\n<p>Using the IBAN validator and parser offers several advantages and useful features:</p>\n<ul>\n    <li><b>Accurate Validation:</b> It checks IBANs against the official standards, giving you confidence in their correctness.</li>\n    <li><b>Detailed Parsing:</b> It breaks down the IBAN into its constituent parts, such as the country code, bank code, and account number (BBAN), making the structure clear.</li>\n    <li><b>QR-IBAN Identification:</b> It specifically checks if the IBAN is a QR-IBAN, which is relevant for certain payment systems.</li>\n    <li><b>Friendly Formatting:</b> It presents the IBAN in a more readable format, often grouped with spaces, which helps prevent errors when manually copying or comparing numbers.</li>\n    <li><b>Saves Time:</b> Get instant results without needing complex software or manual lookups.</li>\n    <li><b>Reduces Errors:</b> By verifying the IBAN upfront, you significantly decrease the risk of failed transactions or misdirected payments.</li>\n    <li><b>Free and Accessible:</b> As an online tool, it\'s freely available anytime you need it, without any installation required.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>\n    <i>"Always validate an IBAN before sending a payment to avoid potential issues!"</i></p>\n<p>We hope this tool proves useful for your banking needs. Feel free to use it whenever you need to check an IBAN. If you have any feedback or suggestions, please let us know!</p>',
            description:
                'Validate and parse IBAN numbers. Check if an IBAN is valid and get the country, BBAN, if it is a QR-IBAN and the IBAN friendly format.',
